"Here are the answers to the questions:\n\n***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\n1. Not very likely\n\nBond has been caught and disarmed, and he is being held by Le Chiffre and his two gunmen. It seems unlikely that he will be able to escape at this point.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n6. Very suspenseful\n\nThe passage is suspenseful because Bond has been caught and is being held captive by Le Chiffre and his men. The reader is left wondering what will happen to Bond next and whether he will be able to escape or not. The use of action and tension, such as the fight between Bond and the Corsican, adds to the suspense."